---
title: Spinach and Mushroom Orzo with sprinkled walnuts
description: Whether it's the al dente orzo or the amount of delicious veg packed inside, this is an inherently comforting dish. Serve piled high in bowls and finished off with a sprinkling of walnuts for added taste and texture.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/HF_Y23_R10_W28_IE_IEXVV0124-4_Main_high_edit-0f57cf33.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.ie/recipecards/card/646f85450c1e02e39244a384.pdf
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 569 kcal
  fat: 20.8 g
  saturated fat: 8.7 g
  carbohydrates: 75.7 g
  sugar: 8.9 g
  protein: 20.9 g
  sodium: 4 g
  serving size: 305
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: Italian
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.ie/recipes/spinach-and-mushroom-orzo-646f85450c1e02e39244a384
course: main course
---

Roughly chop the @mushrooms{150%g}.

Trim the @leek{1/2}, then halve lengthways. Thinly slice half (double for 4p)
widthways.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly chop the @baby spinach{60%g}.

Place a large #pot{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. When hot, add
the leek and mushrooms. Season with @salt{}.

Cook until softened, stirring occasionally, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the garlic and cook, stirring constantly, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @dried orzo{170%g}, @Hello Muscat{2%sachets}, @water{400%ml} and
@butter{1%tbsp} (double both for 4p) to the pot. Bring to the boil, cover and
simmer until the orzo is al dente, ~{15-20%minutes}. Stir every 3-4 mins to
prevent sticking.

When the orzo is cooked, add the @grated Italian style hard cheese{25%g},
@creme fraiche{65%g} and spinach to the pot. Stir until spinach is wilted,
~{3-4%minutes}. Add a splash of water to loosen the sauce if required. Season
to taste with salt and @pepper{}.

Roughly chop the @walnuts{20%g}.

Divide your veggie orzo between #bowls{}. Finish with a scattering of walnuts.

> Whether it's the al dente orzo or the amount of delicious veg packed inside,
> this is an inherently comforting dish. Serve piled high in bowls and finished
> off with a sprinkling of walnuts for added taste and texture.